$PAR
Consider the functions given by \(f(x) = 5-(x-1)^2\) and \(g(x) = 4-x\).
(a) Use algebra to find the points where the graphs of \(f\) and \(g\) intersect. $BR 
\{ essay_box(4,60) \}
$PAR
(b) Sketch an accurate graph of \(f\) and $g$ on the axes provided, labeling the curves by name and the intersection points with ordered pairs. $BR 
\{ essay_box(4,60) \}
$PAR
(c) Find and evaluate exactly an integral expression that represents the area between \(y = f(x)\) and the \(x\)-axis on the interval between the intersection points of \(f\) and \(g\). $BR 
\{ essay_box(4,60) \}
$PAR
(d) Find and evaluate exactly an integral expression that represents the area between \(y = g(x)\) and the \(x\)-axis on the interval between the intersection points of \(f\) and \(g\).  $BR 
\{ essay_box(4,60) \}
$PAR
(e) What is the exact area between \(f) and \(g\) between their intersection points?  Why? $BR 
\{ essay_box(4,60) \}
$PAR



